=3D12
v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_11"><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>De=
fending
troops will naturally lead the defense of their colony. However the populat=
ion
of the colony will also join in the fight, adding their strength to fight o=
ff
your invasion. Each 500 million citizens of a colonies population are rough=
ly
equivalent to a single defending troop.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>However note that if =
a colony
has no defending troops the population will not rise up to defend the colon=
y.
They will consider this to be a hopeless situation and resign themselves to
becoming part of the invading empire.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>When a ground battle =
is in
progress each side may have bonuses or penalties to their defend or attack
strength. These bonuses or penalties relate to the composition of their for=
ces,
the type of planet and other factors.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Strategy<o:p></o:p></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>For an invasion to su=
cceed,
the invading troops should significantly outnumber the defenders. Prolonged
battles can weaken invading troops &#8211; even if they eventually win the
invasion it will take some time to recuperate their readiness. Quickly over=
whelming
the defenders with irresistible force is the best strategy.<o:p></o:p></spa=
n></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_12" o:=
spid=3D"_x0000_s1027"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:51.9pt;margin-=
top:0;
 width:103.1pt;height:103.7pt;z-index:251657728;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_CombatGround_files/image003.png" o:title=
=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D137 height=3D138
src=3D"GameConcepts_CombatGround_files/image004.png" align=3Dright hspace=
=3D12
v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_12"><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Yo=
u should
also attempt to land your invading forces simultaneously, or as close to th=
is
as possible. Piecemeal deployment of invading troops will mean they get pic=
ked
off individually by the defenders, greatly diluting their impact.<o:p></o:p=
></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Resolving the battle<o:p></o:p></span>=
</h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>When the troops of ei=
ther
side have been completely eliminated then the battle is over.<o:p></o:p></s=
pan></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>If the troops of the
defending empire have been wiped out then the invading empire takes over the
colony, adding it to their own empire. Any bases at the colony (e.g. space
ports) are also immediately taken over by the invading empire.<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>If the troops of the =
invader
are wiped out then the defending empire keeps its colony, though some of its
troops may have been lost, and some of its population killed in the fightin=
g.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>In either case &#8211;
whether the invader or defender wins &#8211; the colonies development level
will be temporarily set back by the disruption.<o:p></o:p></span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><!--[if gte vml 1]><v:shape id=3D"Picture_x0020_2" o:s=
pid=3D"_x0000_s1026"
 type=3D"#_x0000_t75" style=3D'position:absolute;margin-left:232.1pt;margin=
-top:0;
 width:283.3pt;height:260.6pt;z-index:251658752;visibility:visible;
 mso-wrap-style:square;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent:0;
 mso-wrap-distance-left:9pt;mso-wrap-distance-top:0;mso-wrap-distance-right=
:9pt;
 mso-wrap-distance-bottom:0;mso-position-horizontal:right;
 mso-position-horizontal-relative:text;mso-position-vertical:absolute;
 mso-position-vertical-relative:text;mso-width-percent:0;mso-height-percent=
:0;
 mso-width-relative:page;mso-height-relative:page'>
 <v:imagedata src=3D"GameConcepts_CombatGround_files/image007.png" o:title=
=3D""/>
 <w:wrap type=3D"square"/>
</v:shape><![endif]--><![if !vml]><img width=3D378 height=3D347
src=3D"GameConcepts_CombatGround_files/image005.png" align=3Dright hspace=
=3D12
v:shapes=3D"Picture_x0020_2"><![endif]><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Vic=
torious
troops (of either invader or defender) also receive a promotion &#8211; the=
ir
strength will increase, making them more effective in future battles.<o:p><=
/o:p></span></p>

<h3><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>Monitoring a ground invasion<o:p></o:p=
></span></h3>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You can monitor the p=
rogress
of a ground invasion by selecting the colony. The colony information will be
displayed in the Selection Panel at the bottom-left of the main view. Defen=
ding
troops will appear here in the &#8220;Troops&#8221; section. Invading troops
will also appear here &#8211; they will have a red background.<o:p></o:p></=
span></p>

<p class=3DMsoNormal><span style=3D'mso-no-proof:yes'>You can also display a
detailed animated view of ground battles by opening the Ground Report scree=
n.
To open this screen first select the colony in the Selection Panel, then cl=
ick
the Troops area in the Selection Panel.</span></p>

